    {
      "id": "d94d4b94_d45ca50f",
      "file_path": "robot/resources/demo_preload.robot",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 57,
      "message": "We can have different values for id and name, I'll test it and cover.\n\n\nIn terms of global variables, I'm against it, so it can be in line with flow used for VNF-based init.\nIn current approach, we can load several Clouds, that share the same customer/cloud-owner/location (that are defined globally or passed as parameters), but differ on region/tenant level. I'd like to improve this preloading in future, so that robot can create k8s cloud and load its credentials to be usable by k8splugin (based on the same way, as currently it takes openstack credentials), but registered as separate cloud.\n\nIn general, it could be set globally, but I wanted to keep my changes to be as much similar to VNF-init-flow as possible",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5550,
        "name": "Konrad Banka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kbanka.os@gmail.com",
        "username": "kbanka"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-18 11:27:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0010869c_adfc736d",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "07c7590c_8526ea0e",
      "file_path": "robot/resources/demo_preload.robot",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 80,
      "message": "Well, I think k8s-based vFW demo will straightly evolve to use CDS, so there won't be any other/separate demos. I just wanted to use unique codename, that everyone would understand what is it about. I can of course remove '_CDS', but I think '_CNF' suffix should stay.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5550,
        "name": "Konrad Banka",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "kbanka.os@gmail.com",
        "username": "kbanka"
      },
      "updated": "2019-10-18 11:27:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "e8c55a7f_a9d292ad",
      "unresolved": true
    },
